This paper belongs to the field of network science and analysis, which can be applied to various subfields of computer science. The paper specifically analyzes the structure of Wikipedia's First Link Network, which involves algorithms and data analysis (cs.SI). The paper also involves measuring the accumulation of links and path lengths, which falls under the category of data mining (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper discusses the influence of articles in shaping the network, which can be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). Finally, the paper touches on the topic of cycles in directed networks, which can be related to the field of control theory (cs.CY).
